 statistics are in (with debuffs)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Tears of Ro - level 61 Fire based rain spell (-10 fire resist check) using Malo or Malosini</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre>         
3 waves resisted:  2
2 waves resisted: 15
1 wave  resisted: 67
0 waves resisted: 76

160 Tears of Ro cast = 3 x 160 waves = 480 total waves
6 + 30 + 67 = 103 waves fully resisted

103/480 = 21.46% full resist rate
(0 waves partially resisted)

3 x 750 = 2250 damage per cast
2250 damage/400 mana = 5.625 dd/mana ratio
5.625 x 21.46% = 1.207 resist reduction
</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END--><br>
<br>
5.625 - 1.207 = <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>4.418 adjusted damage/mana ratio for Tears of Ro using Malo or Malosini</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
NOTES:<br>
Data was collected from the Plane of Valor MoBs that are in the Waste Lands areas.  Their levels ranged between ~61-63.  All Tears of Ro casts were preceded by either <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=1578&amp;source=Live">Malo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> or <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=3387&amp;source=Live">Malosini</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.  There might have been a small decrease in total resists when malosini was being used but I would not call it significant.  About half of the data was collected using Malo and the other half using Malosini.  No partial resists were observed.<br>
<br>
